snippet: Fifth-seeded Angelique Kerber of Germany defeated Madison Keys in a third-round match at the Australian Open. And No. 4 Agnieszka Radwanska and sixth-seeded Li Na advanced to the fourth round.
abstract: Angelique Kerber defeats Madison Keys to advance to fourth-round of Australian Open tennis tournament; other matches noted.
lead_paragraph: Fifth-seeded Angelique Kerber of Germany defeated Madison Keys in a third-round match at the Australian Open. And No. 4 Agnieszka Radwanska and sixth-seeded Li Na advanced to the fourth round.

headline.seo: Angelique Kerber Defeats Madison Keys at Australian Open
headline.main: American Teenager Loses in Straight Sets to Kerber
